{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":365,"text":"What I want to talk to you about today"},{"time":2396,"text":"is some of the problems that the military\nof the Western world --"},{"time":7000,"text":"Australia, United States,\nthe UK and so on --"},{"time":9761,"text":"face in some of the deployments\nthat they're dealing with"},{"time":12915,"text":"in the modern world at this time."},{"time":14843,"text":"If you think about the sorts of things"},{"time":16691,"text":"we've sent Australian military\npersonnel to in recent years,"},{"time":19812,"text":"we've got obvious things\nlike Iraq and Afghanistan,"},{"time":22229,"text":"but you've also got things like\nEast Timor and the Solomon Islands,"},{"time":25421,"text":"and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26598,"text":"And a lot of these deployments"},{"time":28058,"text":"that we're sending\nmilitary personnel to these days"},{"time":31216,"text":"aren't traditional wars."},{"time":33353,"text":"In fact, a lot of the jobs\nwe're asking military personnel to do"},{"time":37464,"text":"in those situations"},{"time":38639,"text":"are ones that, in their own countries --\nAustralia, the US and so on --"},{"time":42239,"text":"would actually be done by police officers."},{"time":44632,"text":"So there's a bunch\nof problems that come up"},{"time":46684,"text":"for military personnel\nin these situations,"},{"time":48716,"text":"because they're doing things\nthey haven't really been trained for."},{"time":51991,"text":"And they're doing things that those\nwho do them in their own countries"},{"time":56827,"text":"are trained very differently for\nand equipped very differently for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60506,"text":"Now, there's a bunch of reasons\nwhy we send military personnel,"},{"time":64193,"text":"rather than police, to do these jobs."},{"time":66415,"text":"If Australia had to send\n1,000 people tomorrow"},{"time":69000,"text":"to West Papua, for example,"},{"time":71799,"text":"we don't have 1,000 police officers\nhanging around that could go tomorrow,"},{"time":75650,"text":"and we do have\n1,000 soldiers that could go."},{"time":78251,"text":"So when we have to send someone,\nwe send the military --"},{"time":80935,"text":"they're there, they're available,"},{"time":82536,"text":"and heck, they're used to going off\nand doing these things"},{"time":85293,"text":"and living by themselves"},{"time":86560,"text":"and not having all this extra support."},{"time":88422,"text":"So they are able to do it in that sense."},{"time":91106,"text":"But they aren't trained\nthe same way police officers are,"},{"time":93960,"text":"and they're certainly not equipped\nthe way police officers are,"},{"time":96980,"text":"so this has raised\na bunch of problems for them"},{"time":99196,"text":"when dealing with these issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100706,"text":"One particular thing that's come up\nthat I am especially interested in,"},{"time":104088,"text":"is the question of whether,"},{"time":105739,"text":"when we're sending military personnel\nto do these sorts of jobs,"},{"time":108803,"text":"we ought to be equipping them differently;"},{"time":110857,"text":"and in particular, whether we ought\nto be giving them access"},{"time":113746,"text":"to some of the nonlethal weapons\nthat police have."},{"time":116186,"text":"Since they're doing some of the same jobs,"},{"time":118289,"text":"maybe they should have\nsome of those things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120371,"text":"And there's a range of places you'd think\nthose things would be really useful."},{"time":124094,"text":"For example, when you've got\nmilitary checkpoints."},{"time":126701,"text":"If people are approaching\nthese checkpoints"},{"time":128740,"text":"and the military personnel are unsure\nif this person's hostile or not,"},{"time":132389,"text":"say this person approaching\nhere, and they say,"},{"time":134767,"text":"\"Is this a suicide bomber or not?"},{"time":136387,"text":"Is something hidden under their clothes?"},{"time":138377,"text":"What's going to happen?\""},{"time":139555,"text":"They don't know if the person\nis hostile or not."},{"time":141831,"text":"If the person doesn't follow directions,\nthey may end up shooting them,"},{"time":145242,"text":"and then find out afterwards\neither, yes, we shot the right person,"},{"time":148481,"text":"or, no, this was just an innocent person"},{"time":150450,"text":"who didn't understand what was going on."},{"time":152606,"text":"So if they had nonlethal weapons,\nthen they would say,"},{"time":155236,"text":"\"We can use them\nin that sort of situation."},{"time":157287,"text":"If we shoot someone who wasn't hostile,"},{"time":159199,"text":"at least we haven't killed them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":161072,"text":"Another situation: this photo\nis from one of the missions"},{"time":164351,"text":"in the Balkans in the late 1990s."},{"time":166765,"text":"This situation is a little bit different,"},{"time":168766,"text":"where maybe they know someone is hostile;"},{"time":170751,"text":"they've got someone shooting at them"},{"time":172493,"text":"or doing something else\nthat's clearly hostile,"},{"time":174714,"text":"throwing rocks, whatever."},{"time":175970,"text":"But if they respond,"},{"time":177145,"text":"there's a range of other people around\nwho are innocent people,"},{"time":180162,"text":"who might also get hurt."},{"time":181341,"text":"It'd be collateral damage"},{"time":182592,"text":"that the military\noften doesn't want to talk about."},{"time":185333,"text":"So again, they'd say, \"With access\nto nonlethal weapons,"},{"time":188116,"text":"if we've got someone we know is hostile,"},{"time":190073,"text":"we can do something to deal with them,"},{"time":191930,"text":"and know that if we hit anyone else,"},{"time":193716,"text":"at least we're not going to kill them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":196091,"text":"Another suggestion has been,"},{"time":197551,"text":"since we're putting so many\nrobots in the field,"},{"time":199862,"text":"we can see the time coming"},{"time":201156,"text":"where they're actually going\nto send robots out in the field"},{"time":204048,"text":"that are autonomous."},{"time":205226,"text":"They'll make their own decisions\nabout who to shoot and who not to shoot,"},{"time":208729,"text":"without a human in the loop."},{"time":210095,"text":"So the suggestion is,"},{"time":211431,"text":"if we're going to send robots out\nand allow them to do this,"},{"time":214569,"text":"maybe it would be a good idea\nif they were armed with nonlethal weapons,"},{"time":218851,"text":"so if the robot makes a bad decision\nand shoots the wrong person,"},{"time":221988,"text":"again, they haven't actually killed them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224632,"text":"Now, there's a whole range\nof different sorts of nonlethal weapons,"},{"time":227872,"text":"some of which are available now,"},{"time":229497,"text":"some of which they're developing."},{"time":231113,"text":"You've got traditional things\nlike pepper spray,"},{"time":233415,"text":"OC spray up at the top there,"},{"time":234920,"text":"or Tasers over here."},{"time":236798,"text":"The one on the top right here\nis actually a dazzling laser,"},{"time":239974,"text":"intended to just blind\nthe person momentarily"},{"time":242613,"text":"and disorient them."},{"time":244247,"text":"You've got nonlethal shotgun rounds"},{"time":246263,"text":"that contain rubber pellets\ninstead of the traditional metal ones."},{"time":249706,"text":"And this one in the middle\nhere, the large truck,"},{"time":252313,"text":"is called the Active Denial System,"},{"time":254707,"text":"something the US military\nis working on at the moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257351,"text":"It's essentially a big\nmicrowave transmitter."},{"time":260794,"text":"It's sort of your classic\nidea of a heat ray."},{"time":263947,"text":"It goes out to a really long distance,"},{"time":266600,"text":"compared to any of these\nother sorts of things."},{"time":268863,"text":"Anybody who is hit with this\nfeels a sudden burst of heat,"},{"time":272713,"text":"and just wants to get out of the way."},{"time":274848,"text":"It is a lot more sophisticated\nthan a microwave oven,"},{"time":277496,"text":"but it basically is boiling\nthe water molecules"},{"time":280402,"text":"in the very surface level of your skin."},{"time":282378,"text":"So you feel this massive heat,"},{"time":284148,"text":"and you go, \"I want\nto get out of the way.\""},{"time":286584,"text":"And they think this will be really useful"},{"time":288588,"text":"in places where we need to clear\na crowd out of a particular area,"},{"time":291757,"text":"if the crowd is being hostile."},{"time":293230,"text":"If we need to keep people\naway from a particular place,"},{"time":295865,"text":"we can do that with these sorts of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298360,"text":"So there's a whole range\nof different nonlethal weapons"},{"time":301421,"text":"we could give military personnel,"},{"time":303385,"text":"and there's a whole range of situations"},{"time":305316,"text":"where they're looking at them and saying,"},{"time":307293,"text":"\"These things would be really useful.\""},{"time":309152,"text":"But as I said,"},{"time":310580,"text":"the military and the police\nare very different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313593,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":314649,"text":"Yes, you don't have to look\nvery hard at this to recognize"},{"time":317404,"text":"that they might be very different."},{"time":319196,"text":"In particular,"},{"time":320490,"text":"the attitude to the use of force"},{"time":322194,"text":"and the way they're trained to use force"},{"time":324286,"text":"is especially different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326976,"text":"The police --"},{"time":328600,"text":"and knowing because I've actually\nhelped to train police --"},{"time":331636,"text":"police, particularly\nin Western jurisdictions at least,"},{"time":334398,"text":"are trained to De-escalate force,"},{"time":338265,"text":"to try and avoid using force\nwherever possible,"},{"time":341234,"text":"and to use lethal force\nonly as an absolute last resort."},{"time":346441,"text":"Military personnel\nare being trained for war."},{"time":349600,"text":"So they're trained that,\nas soon as things go bad,"},{"time":352711,"text":"their first response is lethal force."},{"time":356400,"text":"The moment the fecal matter\nhits the rotating turbine --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":359492,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":360548,"text":"you can start shooting at people."},{"time":363753,"text":"So their attitudes"},{"time":365600,"text":"to the use of lethal force\nare very different,"},{"time":368017,"text":"and I think it's fairly obvious"},{"time":369660,"text":"that their attitude to the use\nof nonlethal weapons"},{"time":372600,"text":"would also be very different\nfrom what it is with the police."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376177,"text":"And since we've already had\nso many problems"},{"time":378302,"text":"with police use of nonlethal\nweapons in various ways,"},{"time":380947,"text":"I thought it would be a good idea\nto look at some of those things"},{"time":384049,"text":"and relate it to the military context."},{"time":385894,"text":"I was very surprised when I started\nto do this to see that, in fact,"},{"time":389600,"text":"even the people who advocated the use\nof nonlethal weapons by the military"},{"time":393255,"text":"hadn't actually done that."},{"time":394600,"text":"They generally seemed to think,"},{"time":396153,"text":"\"Why would we care\nwhat's happened with the police?"},{"time":398729,"text":"We're looking at something different,\""},{"time":400575,"text":"and didn't seem to recognize"},{"time":402011,"text":"they were looking at pretty\nmuch the same stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404482,"text":"So I started to investigate\nsome of those issues,"},{"time":407290,"text":"and have a look at the way\npolice use nonlethal weapons"},{"time":411067,"text":"when they're introduced,"},{"time":412249,"text":"and some of the problems that might\narise out of those sorts of things"},{"time":415600,"text":"when they actually do introduce them."},{"time":417651,"text":"And of course, being Australian,"},{"time":420234,"text":"I started looking at stuff in Australia,\nknowing from my own experience"},{"time":424026,"text":"of various times when nonlethal weapons\nhave been introduced in Australia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427866,"text":"One of the things I particularly\nlooked at was the use of OC spray --"},{"time":431356,"text":"oleoresin capsicum spray, pepper spray --"},{"time":433893,"text":"by Australian police,"},{"time":435849,"text":"and seeing what had happened\nwhen that had been introduced,"},{"time":438684,"text":"and those sorts of issues."},{"time":440187,"text":"And one study that I found,\na particularly interesting one,"},{"time":443317,"text":"was in Queensland,"},{"time":445238,"text":"because they had a trial period\nfor the use of pepper spray"},{"time":448687,"text":"before they actually\nintroduced it more broadly."},{"time":451732,"text":"And I went and had a look\nat some of the figures here."},{"time":454605,"text":"Now, when they introduced\nOC spray in Queensland,"},{"time":457136,"text":"they were really explicit."},{"time":458732,"text":"The police minister's and a heap\nof public statements were made about it."},{"time":462252,"text":"They were saying, \"This is explicitly\nintended to give police an option"},{"time":465669,"text":"between shouting and shooting."},{"time":468858,"text":"This is something they can use\ninstead of a firearm"},{"time":471600,"text":"in situations where they would have\npreviously had to shoot someone.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":474893,"text":"So I looked at all\nof the police shooting figures."},{"time":477600,"text":"And you can't actually\nfind them very easily"},{"time":479720,"text":"for individual Australian states;"},{"time":481600,"text":"I could only find these."},{"time":483140,"text":"This is from an Australian Institute\nof Criminology report."},{"time":485963,"text":"You can see, in the fine print at the top:"},{"time":487995,"text":"\"Police shooting deaths\"\nmeans not just people shot by police,"},{"time":491244,"text":"but people who have shot themselves\nin the presence of police."},{"time":494298,"text":"But these are the figures\nacross the entire country,"},{"time":496773,"text":"and the red arrow represents\nthe point where Queensland said,"},{"time":499901,"text":"\"Yes, this is where we're going to give"},{"time":501819,"text":"all police officers\nacross the entire state"},{"time":503983,"text":"access to OC spray.\""},{"time":505510,"text":"So you can see there were six deaths\nsort of leading up to it,"},{"time":508600,"text":"every year for a number of years."},{"time":510695,"text":"There was a spike a few years before,"},{"time":512600,"text":"but that wasn't actually Queensland."},{"time":514466,"text":"Anyone know where that was?"},{"time":516121,"text":"Wasn't Port Arthur, no."},{"time":517766,"text":"Victoria? Yes, correct."},{"time":519868,"text":"That spike was all Victoria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521869,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":523044,"text":"So it wasn't that Queensland\nhad a particular problem"},{"time":525632,"text":"with deaths from police\nshootings and so on."},{"time":528351,"text":"So, six shootings\nacross the whole country,"},{"time":530788,"text":"fairly consistently over the years before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532849,"text":"The next two years were the years\nthey studied -- 2001, 2002."},{"time":535825,"text":"Anyone want to take a stab\nat the number of times,"},{"time":538761,"text":"given how they've introduced this,"},{"time":540441,"text":"the number of times police in Queensland\nused OC spray in that period?"},{"time":543933,"text":"Hundreds? One? Three?"},{"time":546425,"text":"A thousand is getting better."},{"time":550471,"text":"Explicitly introduced as an alternative\nto the use of lethal force --"},{"time":554481,"text":"an alternative between\nshouting and shooting."},{"time":557219,"text":"I'm going to go out on a limb here"},{"time":559220,"text":"and say that if Queensland police\ndidn't have OC spray,"},{"time":562532,"text":"they wouldn't have shot 2,226 people"},{"time":565337,"text":"in those two years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566732,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":569222,"text":"In fact, if you have a look\nat the studies they were looking at,"},{"time":572445,"text":"the material they were\ncollecting and examining,"},{"time":575751,"text":"you can see the suspects were only armed\nin about 15 percent of cases"},{"time":580387,"text":"where OC spray was used."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582819,"text":"It was routinely being\nused in this period,"},{"time":585481,"text":"and, of course, still is routinely used --"},{"time":587624,"text":"because there were no complaints about it,"},{"time":590030,"text":"not within the context\nof this study, anyway --"},{"time":593152,"text":"it was routinely being used\nto deal with people who were violent,"},{"time":596988,"text":"who were potentially violent,"},{"time":598715,"text":"and also quite frequently used"},{"time":601056,"text":"to deal with people who were\nsimply passively noncompliant."},{"time":606222,"text":"This person is not doing anything violent,"},{"time":608331,"text":"but they just won't do\nwhat we want them to."},{"time":610440,"text":"They're not obeying\nthe directions we're giving them,"},{"time":612977,"text":"so we'll give them a shot\nof the OC spray -- that'll speed them up."},{"time":616153,"text":"Everything will work out better that way."},{"time":618704,"text":"This was something explicitly introduced"},{"time":621132,"text":"to be an alternative to firearms,"},{"time":622988,"text":"but it's being routinely used"},{"time":624989,"text":"to deal with a whole range\nof other sorts of problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628466,"text":"Now one of the particular\nissues that comes up"},{"time":630814,"text":"with military use of nonlethal weapons --"},{"time":633600,"text":"and people actually say,\n\"There might be some problems\" --"},{"time":636543,"text":"there's a couple of particular\nproblems that get focused on."},{"time":639961,"text":"One of those problems is: nonlethal\nweapons may be used indiscriminately."},{"time":645136,"text":"One of the fundamental principles\nof military use of force"},{"time":648381,"text":"is that you have to be discriminate;"},{"time":650173,"text":"you have to be careful\nabout who you're shooting at."},{"time":652950,"text":"So one of the problems suggested\nwith nonlethal weapons"},{"time":655600,"text":"is that they might be used\nindiscriminately --"},{"time":657815,"text":"that you would use them\nagainst a whole range of people,"},{"time":660475,"text":"because you don't have\nto worry so much anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662804,"text":"And in fact, one particular instance\nwhere I think that actually happens"},{"time":666439,"text":"was the Dubrovka Theater\nsiege in Moscow in 2002,"},{"time":669321,"text":"which probably a lot of you,\nunlike most of my students at ADFA,"},{"time":672360,"text":"are old enough to remember."},{"time":673977,"text":"So, Chechens had come in\nand taken control of the theater."},{"time":676762,"text":"They were holding something\nlike 700 people hostage."},{"time":680094,"text":"They'd released a bunch of people,"},{"time":681748,"text":"but they still had\nabout 700 people hostage."},{"time":684138,"text":"And the Russian military police\nspecial forces, \"Spetsnaz,\""},{"time":689600,"text":"came in and stormed the theater."},{"time":691600,"text":"The way they did it was to pump\nthe whole thing full of anesthetic gas."},{"time":695067,"text":"And it turned out\nthat lots of the hostages died"},{"time":699693,"text":"as a result of inhaling the gas."},{"time":702481,"text":"It was used indiscriminately."},{"time":704600,"text":"They pumped the whole theater\nfull of the gas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707489,"text":"And it's no surprise that people died,"},{"time":710203,"text":"because you don't know how much gas\neach person is going to inhale,"},{"time":713600,"text":"what position they'll fall in when\nthey become unconscious, and so on."},{"time":717519,"text":"There were, in fact,\nonly a couple of people who got shot"},{"time":720600,"text":"in this episode."},{"time":722600,"text":"So when they had a look at it afterward,"},{"time":724600,"text":"there were only a couple of people\nwho'd apparently been shot,"},{"time":727566,"text":"by the hostage takers\nor by the police forces"},{"time":730466,"text":"trying to deal with the situation."},{"time":732496,"text":"Virtually everybody that got killed"},{"time":734227,"text":"got killed from inhaling the gas."},{"time":737123,"text":"The final toll of hostages\nis a little unclear,"},{"time":740475,"text":"but it's certainly a few more than that,"},{"time":742427,"text":"because other people died\nover the next few days."},{"time":744740,"text":"So this was one problem they talked about,"},{"time":746811,"text":"that it might be used indiscriminately."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748699,"text":"A second problem\npeople sometimes talk about"},{"time":750968,"text":"with military use of nonlethal weapons --"},{"time":752960,"text":"and it's actually why,\nin the chemical weapons convention,"},{"time":755863,"text":"it's very clear that you can't use\nriot-control agents"},{"time":758460,"text":"as weapons of warfare --"},{"time":759773,"text":"is that it's seen that sometimes\nnonlethal weapons might be used"},{"time":763826,"text":"not as an alternative to lethal force,"},{"time":765771,"text":"but as a lethal force multiplier:"},{"time":768714,"text":"that you use nonlethal weapons first,"},{"time":770679,"text":"so your lethal weapons\nwill actually be more effective."},{"time":774157,"text":"The people you'll be shooting at\nwon't be able to get out of the way."},{"time":777537,"text":"They won't be aware of what's happening,\nand you can kill them better."},{"time":780954,"text":"And that's exactly what happened here."},{"time":783691,"text":"The hostage takers who had\nbeen rendered unconscious by the gas"},{"time":786771,"text":"were not taken into custody;"},{"time":788213,"text":"they were simply shot in the head."},{"time":791531,"text":"So this nonlethal weapon\nwas being used in this case"},{"time":795600,"text":"as a lethal force multiplier,"},{"time":798600,"text":"to make killing more effective\nin this particular situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803440,"text":"Another problem I want to quickly mention"},{"time":805845,"text":"is that there's a whole heap of problems"},{"time":808099,"text":"with the way people are actually\ntaught to use nonlethal weapons,"},{"time":811600,"text":"and get trained about them\nand then tested and so on."},{"time":814157,"text":"Because they're tested\nin nice, safe environments,"},{"time":817056,"text":"and are taught to use them\nin nice, safe environments --"},{"time":819717,"text":"like this, where you can see\nexactly what's going on."},{"time":823026,"text":"The person spraying the OC spray\nis wearing a rubber glove"},{"time":825825,"text":"to make sure they don't get\ncontaminated, and so on."},{"time":828291,"text":"But they're never used like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829926,"text":"They're used out in the real world,"},{"time":832118,"text":"like in Texas, like this:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":834476,"text":"[\"Police Taser Great-Grandmother\nDuring Traffic Stop\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":837090,"text":"I confess, this particular case\nwas one that piqued my interest in this."},{"time":840600,"text":"It happened while I was working\nas a research fellow"},{"time":843072,"text":"at the US Naval Academy."},{"time":844284,"text":"News reports started\ncoming up about this situation,"},{"time":847285,"text":"where this woman was arguing\nwith a police officer."},{"time":849709,"text":"She wasn't violent."},{"time":851116,"text":"In fact, he was probably\nsix inches taller than me,"},{"time":854053,"text":"and she was about this tall."},{"time":856372,"text":"And eventually she said to him,"},{"time":858103,"text":"\"Well, I'm going to get back in my car.\""},{"time":860228,"text":"And he says, \"If you get back\nin your car, I'm going to tase you.\""},{"time":863394,"text":"And she says, \"Oh, go ahead.\nTase me.\" And so he does."},{"time":866538,"text":"And it's all captured by the video camera"},{"time":868577,"text":"running in the front of the police car."},{"time":872176,"text":"So, she's 72."},{"time":875072,"text":"And it's seen that this is the most\nappropriate way of dealing with her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878550,"text":"And there are other examples\nof the same sorts of things,"},{"time":881699,"text":"where you think,"},{"time":882889,"text":"\"Is this really an appropriate way\nto use nonlethal weapons?\""},{"time":886243,"text":"\"Police Chief Fires Taser\ninto 14 year old Girl's Head.\""},{"time":888899,"text":"\"She was running away.\nWhat else was I suppose to do?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":891487,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":893733,"text":"Or Florida:"},{"time":895693,"text":"\"Police Taser 6-year-old\nBoy at Elementary School.\""},{"time":898527,"text":"And they clearly learned a lot from it,\nbecause in the same district:"},{"time":902288,"text":"\"Police Review Policy\nAfter Children Shocked:"},{"time":904953,"text":"2nd Child Shocked by Taser\nStun Gun Within Weeks.\""},{"time":907684,"text":"Same police district."},{"time":909668,"text":"Another child within weeks\nof Tasering the six-year-old boy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912877,"text":"Just in case you think it's only going\nto happen in the United States,"},{"time":916386,"text":"it happened in Canada as well:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":918228,"text":"[\"Mounties Zap 11-year-old Boy\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":919798,"text":"And a colleague sent me\nthis one from London:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":921932,"text":"[\"Arrested Man, 82, Shot with Taser\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":923826,"text":"But my personal favorite,\nI have to confess, does come from the US:"},{"time":928261,"text":"\"Officers Taser 86-year-old\nDisabled Woman in her Bed.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":931577,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":933807,"text":"I checked the reports on this one."},{"time":935935,"text":"I looked at it. I was really surprised."},{"time":938033,"text":"Apparently, she took up a more\nthreatening position in her bed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942225,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":943939,"text":"I kid you not,\nthat's exactly what it said:"},{"time":946012,"text":"\"She took up a more threatening\nposition in her bed.\""},{"time":949366,"text":"OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950706,"text":"But I'd remind you --"},{"time":952175,"text":"I'm talking about military\nuses of nonlethal weapons,"},{"time":954715,"text":"so why is this relevant?"},{"time":955897,"text":"Because police are actually\nmore restrained in the use of force"},{"time":959143,"text":"than the military are."},{"time":960634,"text":"They're trained to be more\nrestrained in the use of force"},{"time":963344,"text":"than the military are."},{"time":964538,"text":"They're trained to think more,\nto try and De-escalate."},{"time":967104,"text":"So if you have these problems\nwith police officers"},{"time":969475,"text":"with nonlethal weapons,"},{"time":970665,"text":"what on earth would make you think"},{"time":972332,"text":"it's going to be better\nwith military personnel?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":975474,"text":"The last thing that I would like to say:"},{"time":978772,"text":"When I'm talking to the police"},{"time":980233,"text":"about what a perfect nonlethal\nweapon would look like,"},{"time":982797,"text":"they almost inevitably say the same thing."},{"time":984835,"text":"They say, \"It's got to be something\nthat's nasty enough"},{"time":987541,"text":"that people don't want\nto be hit with this weapon."},{"time":990005,"text":"So if you threaten to use it,"},{"time":991432,"text":"people are going to comply with it."},{"time":994496,"text":"But it's also going to be something"},{"time":996428,"text":"that doesn't leave any lasting effects.\""},{"time":1001034,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":1002215,"text":"your perfect nonlethal weapon\nis something that's perfect for abuse."},{"time":1005841,"text":"What would these guys have done\nif they'd had access to Tasers,"},{"time":1009414,"text":"or to a manned, portable version\nof the Active Denial System --"},{"time":1013699,"text":"a small heat ray that you\ncan use on people"},{"time":1016187,"text":"and not worry about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018543,"text":"So I think yes,"},{"time":1020224,"text":"there may be ways that nonlethal weapons\nwill be great in these situations,"},{"time":1023798,"text":"but there's also a whole heap of problems"},{"time":1025781,"text":"that need to be considered as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027703,"text":"Thanks very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028887,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}